metadata.name: Entry::Operation
metadata.description:
Operation

Additional information about a potentially long-running operation with which a log entry is associated.

metadata.name: id
metadata.description: An arbitrary operation identifier. Log entries with the same identifier are assumed to be part of the same operation.

metadata.name: id=
metadata.description: An arbitrary operation identifier. Log entries with the same identifier are assumed to be part of the same operation.

metadata.name: producer
metadata.description: An arbitrary producer identifier. The combination of id and producer must be globally unique. Examples for producer: "MyDivision.MyBigCompany.com", "github.com/MyProject/MyApplication".

metadata.name: producer=
metadata.description: An arbitrary producer identifier. The combination of id and producer must be globally unique. Examples for producer: "MyDivision.MyBigCompany.com", "github.com/MyProject/MyApplication".

metadata.name: first
metadata.description: Set this to true if this is the first log entry in the operation.

metadata.name: first=
metadata.description: Set this to true if this is the first log entry in the operation.

metadata.name: last
metadata.description: Set this to true if this is the last log entry in the operation.

metadata.name: last=
metadata.description: Set this to true if this is the last log entry in the operation.
